<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-541-116  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 541 116.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  August 21 1989 v6 n33 p8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Spreadsheet program to provide interfaces to database systems.andO;(Stone Mountain Computing's Graphic Outlook)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Stone Mountain Computing Corp. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   Graphic Outlook (Spreadsheet software) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     EnhancementsData Base Management SystemsSpreadsheetsSoftware PackagesInterface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Spreadsheet Program To Provide Interfaces To Database SystemsandM;GOLETA, Calif.andP;  -- Stone Mountain Computing's Graphic Outlook, a VAX/VMSspreadsheet program, will soon provide interfaces to Oracle and Rdbrelational database management systems, as well as RMS files.andP;  Companyofficials said support for other database products--such as those fromShareBase, InterBase and Relational Technology's Ingres--is forthcoming.andM;&quot;Spreadsheets are going in the direction of interacting with databases.andP;  It'san ideal match to get a bunch of data and put it into a spreadsheet to seewhat trends you have,&quot; said Chris Andrews, Stone Mountain's director ofsoftware.andM;The company's goal is to make database access transparent and effortless forusers, regardless of the data's location, he said.andM;&quot;Future releases of our product are going to have a relational view of dataacross databases.andP;  [Users will] have the illusion that the data residing inseparate databases exists in one table and is database-independent,&quot; Andrewsadded.andM;The target release date for Graphic Outlook with database support is Nov. 1,the officials said.andP;  Prices start at around $1,200.andM;Stone Mountain Computing can be contacted at 42 Aero Camino, Suite 209,Goleta, CA 93117, (805) 968-3838.andO;</TEXT></DOC>